WEBVTT

00:01.669 --> 00:03.204
Previously on The Unit.

00:03.237 --> 00:04.838
You're a reporter
for the Washington Tribune.

00:04.872 --> 00:05.873
We're gonna take you home.

00:05.906 --> 00:07.841
Where exactly is
this T1 line?

00:07.875 --> 00:09.810
They deserve our help.

00:09.843 --> 00:11.979
- [ Muffled Shouting ]
- [ Gunshots ]

00:12.012 --> 00:13.881
- Get a chest tube in me.
- Who's the doctor here?

00:13.914 --> 00:15.983
- [ Shouting ]
- He's unconscious.

00:16.016 --> 00:18.352
Scapula's broken up.
Could've cut the artery.

00:18.386 --> 00:19.987
He's stable,
and the package is secure.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.190
We did it again.
[ Jonas ]
All right, let's go.

00:22.223 --> 00:24.192
[ Gunshot ]

00:24.225 --> 00:27.595
- Sniper.
- Get us out of here.

00:28.862 --> 00:31.432
[ Tires Screeching ]
[ Gunfire ]

00:38.272 --> 00:41.041
- More shooters.
- Heavy guns.

00:41.075 --> 00:42.243
We're not gonna be able
to shake 'em. Reloading.

00:42.276 --> 00:46.046
- I gotta get outta here!
- No. Cuff him.

00:46.080 --> 00:48.516
You talk, I will put
a hood over your head
and strap it down tight.

00:48.549 --> 00:51.552
- You got that?
- Give me your hand grenade.

00:53.721 --> 00:57.091
[ Groans ]

00:57.125 --> 01:01.362
The next time we turn, I want
you to shoot to the left side of
that truck.

01:01.395 --> 01:04.732
I want them to see tracers.
Force 'em wide right.

01:24.252 --> 01:26.287
[ Grey ]
Hector?

01:26.320 --> 01:29.089
Betty Blue,
Hammerhead is gone.

01:29.123 --> 01:32.593
Hammerhead is dead.
You're gonna have
to save yourself now.

01:32.626 --> 01:36.230
- [ Coughing ]
- Breathe. Breathe.

01:36.264 --> 01:39.267
Keep your heart rate down.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.569
Lift your feet up.
Why is that?

01:41.602 --> 01:44.938
Face is red, raise the head.
Face is pale, raise the tail.

01:44.972 --> 01:47.275
Right.
What does that mean?

01:47.308 --> 01:48.942
I gotta keep
the blood in my brain
or I'm gonna die of shock.

01:48.976 --> 01:51.412
Now you're thinking.
What's your mission?

01:51.445 --> 01:53.013
Stay alive, Top.

01:56.950 --> 02:00.321
Dogpatch 0-6,
this is Snake Doctor.

02:00.354 --> 02:03.090
- Status report.
- Send your reports.

02:03.123 --> 02:06.594
One, Kilo, India, Alpha,
Hammerhead.

02:06.627 --> 02:09.663
Whiskey, India, Alpha,
Betty Blue.

02:09.697 --> 02:12.132
Three okay.
Snake Doctor, say again.

02:12.166 --> 02:14.302
Casualties, over.
I say again.

02:14.335 --> 02:16.170
Hammerhead down.

02:19.340 --> 02:22.276
Sergeant Medawar,
alert Graves Registration.

02:22.310 --> 02:25.279
Pull the file
on Sgt. Hector Williams.
Right away.

02:25.313 --> 02:28.516
We are exfilling to
the secondary extraction site.

02:28.549 --> 02:30.818
Confirm the beats.

02:30.851 --> 02:33.887
- Snake Doctor, do you have
the precious cargo?
- Affirmative.

02:38.526 --> 02:43.664
Amigo, you know that
we did not rescue you out
of the kindness of our hearts.

02:43.697 --> 02:45.833
What do you want?
You interviewed Abu Saeef--

02:45.866 --> 02:48.502
- the Butcher.
- Four months ago.

02:48.536 --> 02:50.538
His location?
I don't remember.

02:50.571 --> 02:52.973
You're a journalist.
You're paid to
remember things.

02:53.006 --> 02:56.510
I don't know.
You see this man?

02:56.544 --> 03:00.147
Look at him.
He died for you.
And I kinda liked him.

03:00.180 --> 03:03.551
And it's
the Butcher's people
that did this.

03:03.584 --> 03:06.387
Now I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

03:06.420 --> 03:09.323
What is the location
of the Butcher?

03:09.357 --> 03:11.559
[ Gasping ]

03:11.592 --> 03:14.395
They drove me to a building.

03:14.428 --> 03:19.367
Ten minutes from the Commodore,
up a steep hill,
then it got flat.

03:19.400 --> 03:23.237
I heard airplanes
right above us.
How close?

03:23.271 --> 03:25.506
Ten minutes from his hotel
puts us in this radius.

03:25.539 --> 03:28.509
The planes approach
the airport along
this path.

03:28.542 --> 03:31.712
-The only hill with a direct
line from the approach is here.
-[ Beeping ]

03:31.745 --> 03:35.583
And a plateau...
here.

03:35.616 --> 03:38.386
That's where the Butcher was
four months ago.
No, that's where he is now.

03:38.419 --> 03:40.554
We checked with N.S.A.
There's been chatter
in that location.

03:40.588 --> 03:43.757
- We have a voice signature.
- And a possible visual here.

03:48.596 --> 03:50.464
Flank positions, let's go.

03:52.733 --> 03:55.436
The Butcher's 14 clicks
out from here.

03:55.469 --> 03:57.605
Snake Doctor,
your job's done.
Return to base.

03:57.638 --> 03:59.707
I'm sending in the Bravo team.
They'll clean up the Butcher.

03:59.740 --> 04:04.077
No. This is either a job
for a thousand men or one.

04:04.111 --> 04:06.447
Snake Doctor?

04:06.480 --> 04:08.616
Get him back.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.885
There's no response.
A Mr. Sack, sir--

04:11.919 --> 04:14.422
From the White House.
Which line?

04:21.429 --> 04:23.464
Everybody out.

04:25.966 --> 04:28.736
I just lost a man
on your mission.

04:28.769 --> 04:30.904
Well, we have a problem,
and it's bigger
than one man.

04:30.938 --> 04:33.240
Is that so?
This mission was covert.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.743
Black in, black out.
Your team screwed up.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.945
That was the old plan.
Welcome to the new one.

04:37.978 --> 04:41.949
U.P.I. is going with the story
that American forces
rescued a hostage in Beirut.

04:41.982 --> 04:44.752
The White House denies
American forces
were involved...

04:44.785 --> 04:46.454
because we weren't involved.

04:46.487 --> 04:49.122
Do you read me?

04:49.156 --> 04:50.958
Your team needs to be
out of Beirut now.

04:52.860 --> 04:56.864
[ Chattering ]

05:00.668 --> 05:03.136
[ Man ]
Let's go.
Move it, move it.

05:06.807 --> 05:09.276
[ Man Indistinct ]

05:09.309 --> 05:10.978
Now!
[ Man #2 ]
Yes, sir.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.980
Got the location
of the Butcher.

05:13.013 --> 05:14.815
Let's go get him.
No.

05:14.848 --> 05:18.285
- Get on the boat.
- You can't go there alone.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.788
One man. I'm not gonna
tell your wife
I've lost another.

05:20.821 --> 05:22.856
You want me to tell
your wife? Your wife's
tougher than my wife.

05:22.890 --> 05:24.692
Get in.

05:32.332 --> 05:35.569
[ Outboard Motor Revving ]
I'll see you in Cyprus.

05:46.046 --> 05:49.817
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

05:49.850 --> 05:53.721
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

05:53.754 --> 05:55.823
* See another dawn

05:55.856 --> 05:58.325
* Through a daughter's eyes

05:58.358 --> 06:02.396
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

06:05.365 --> 06:08.068
[ Men Chattering ]

06:10.938 --> 06:13.106
[ Indistinct ]

06:16.109 --> 06:18.712
As-salaam alaikum.

06:19.913 --> 06:22.850
[ Speaking Arabic ]

06:22.883 --> 06:25.853
- [ Man ] American?
- Citizen of the world.
My password is Salma.

06:25.886 --> 06:28.589
- Oh, that's not
today's password.
- It's my password.

06:28.622 --> 06:30.724
- What does it mean?
- Beautiful woman.

06:30.758 --> 06:33.694
[ Chuckling ]

06:33.727 --> 06:36.363
What took you so long?

06:36.396 --> 06:41.435
You know, I wasn't going
to kill you up until right now.

06:41.469 --> 06:44.605
I have something
your boss wants.

06:59.820 --> 07:01.922
[ Grunts ]

07:17.771 --> 07:19.439
How did we
get here, buddy?

07:24.111 --> 07:28.081
If we'd left from the south
exit, we could've...

07:28.115 --> 07:29.950
covered the rooftops
for snipers.

07:36.356 --> 07:39.092
Re-flanked the truck.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.962
Don't bother.
It's not worth the time.

07:45.198 --> 07:48.468
I don't want any toe taggers
touching his body.

07:49.837 --> 07:53.340
One of your men never showed.
Jonas Blane.

07:53.373 --> 07:55.843
Is that so?
Well, here's how I square it.

07:55.876 --> 07:58.278
Either you
purposefully lied to me
or your man's gone rogue.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.614
These are my choices?
Did you order your man back in?

08:00.648 --> 08:02.950
I did.
Is there a reason you
neglected to tell me?

08:02.983 --> 08:05.185
Operational security.
I have A-16 clearance.

08:05.218 --> 08:07.187
How happy you must be.
I have the clearance.

08:07.220 --> 08:08.856
Then you know
what the mission was.
Rescue the hostage.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.457
See if he could lead us
to Abu the Butcher.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.459
Get this Blane character
the hell out of there.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.461
Lost radio contact.
How is that possible?

08:14.494 --> 08:16.797
I told him
to shoot the radio.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.700
I'm telling you that
I'm not wearing a saddle,
so stay off my ass.

08:19.733 --> 08:21.835
You got some loose ends.
Well, what might those be?

08:21.869 --> 08:25.372
The journalist.
Your little secret operation's
gonna end up on CNN.

08:25.405 --> 08:27.040
I've got a checkrein on it.
You'd best have.

08:27.074 --> 08:28.976
The president's going on
national television tonight...

08:29.009 --> 08:31.144
to announce his
Mid-East peace accord.

08:31.178 --> 08:33.847
He calls it his legacy.
So if you can't change
our reporter's mind,

08:33.881 --> 08:36.049
the saddle's going on.

08:46.226 --> 08:48.829
You're wounded.
It's not my blood.

08:48.862 --> 08:52.232
- How is he?
- Somebody did some
heroic field surgery.

08:52.265 --> 08:54.234
A bullet that close
to his artery--
Which one of you?

08:55.769 --> 08:57.838
Well, your friend's
gonna make it.

08:57.871 --> 09:00.107
He's in pain but stable enough
to be medevaced home.

09:04.377 --> 09:08.348
- You look like a rock star.
- I'm drugged up, strung out.

09:08.381 --> 09:12.219
- Looks good on you, dude.
- [ Bob ]
They're gonna medevac you.

09:12.252 --> 09:14.755
- Where's Hector?
- He's right behind you.

09:14.788 --> 09:18.025
- Then I'm staying.
- Look, we're gonna
get you home.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.627
Hector's on his way.

09:27.400 --> 09:29.703
There's a concern
about loose ends.

09:29.737 --> 09:31.705
I understand what
I have to do, Colonel.

09:31.739 --> 09:34.541
The journalist was not rescued
by Americans.

09:34.574 --> 09:37.210
No, sir.

09:37.244 --> 09:39.947
- Tell me what you need.
- He's been "Stockholmed."
Thinks we're the bad guys.

09:39.980 --> 09:42.449
I'm gonna need a couple days
to put his head back
where it belongs.

09:42.482 --> 09:45.052
Eighteen hours he's being fed
to a press conference.

09:45.085 --> 09:47.621
And if we can't
break him down?

09:47.655 --> 09:50.390
Mack will stay
with Williams's body.
Get it cleaned.

09:50.423 --> 09:53.293
- We're running Play 16.
- Roger that.

09:53.326 --> 09:56.263
- Colonel, any word
from Snake Doctor?
- No.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.270
[ Door Opens ]

10:17.117 --> 10:19.119
[ Snap ]

10:20.153 --> 10:22.355
I'm not gonna hurt you.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.101
I do something for you,

10:34.134 --> 10:37.337
you do something for me--
and I need your help.

10:37.370 --> 10:39.973
No, I'm not doing
anything for you.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.477
I'm an American,
and I'm a journalist.

10:44.511 --> 10:46.546
I've got rights.
You can't hold me.
Nobody knows you're here.

10:48.648 --> 10:53.220
As far as the world knows,
you're dead inside prison--
or dead in a ditch.

10:58.358 --> 11:00.360
There's gonna be
a press conference.

11:00.393 --> 11:03.296
At that conference,
we need you to say...

11:03.330 --> 11:06.133
that there were no Americans
involved in your rescue.

11:06.166 --> 11:09.169
- No. I'm not gonna lie.
- We saved your life.
One of our men died for you.

11:09.202 --> 11:12.806
No. I did not ask you to come in
and kick down doors and shoot
innocent people!

11:12.840 --> 11:14.474
Your captors were
going to kill you.
No.

11:14.507 --> 11:16.476
They told me they
weren't gonna kill me.
They lied to you.

11:16.509 --> 11:21.181
They killed 11 hostages
before you.
They are terrorists.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.683
Now, maybe you think
that the Butcher
is a deeply misunderstood man.

11:23.717 --> 11:25.352
But let me tell you something.
He kills Americans.

11:25.385 --> 11:28.155
I got pictures.
You want to see them?

11:28.188 --> 11:31.358
Four months
in that prison, man.
I know they tortured you.

11:33.193 --> 11:35.562
I know it.
I've been tortured.
I know what that's like.

11:35.595 --> 11:38.331
They forced you to say things.
They forced you
to believe things.

11:38.365 --> 11:41.568
I get it.
And now--
And now you want me to lie.

11:41.601 --> 11:45.172
No. No, I want you
to understand the stakes...

11:45.205 --> 11:48.341
to which you expose us
and the next American
in trouble--

11:48.375 --> 11:50.410
The next Granger
that we are tasked
with getting out.

11:53.747 --> 11:55.682
I tell the truth.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.551
- You're a journalist.
- That's right.

11:59.719 --> 12:02.022
Okay, tell me.

12:02.055 --> 12:04.557
Have you ever had to
slant a story in order
to get to a deeper truth?

12:04.591 --> 12:06.559
No.
You're a liar.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.602
- You've lost weight.
- You just never saw me
in this shirt.

12:15.635 --> 12:18.371
You somehow
have gotten uglier.

12:18.405 --> 12:20.607
[ Laughs ]

12:20.640 --> 12:23.777
- Want me to shoot him?
- Mmm. Give him back his guns.

12:26.446 --> 12:28.816
And these guns--
Made in America.

12:30.918 --> 12:33.386
Long way from home.

12:33.420 --> 12:35.455
I need your help.

12:36.623 --> 12:39.559
And what are you offering me?

12:39.592 --> 12:41.461
The Butcher's head.

12:45.933 --> 12:49.636
[ Speaking Arabic ]

12:49.669 --> 12:52.105
- The Butcher can't be found.
- And yet I did it.

12:52.139 --> 12:54.241
I'm half blind
and rolling in money.

12:54.274 --> 12:57.277
I am the enemy of your enemy.

12:57.310 --> 12:59.779
And thus I call you friend.

12:59.813 --> 13:02.115
And you want your friend
to do your dirty work.
No.

13:02.149 --> 13:03.984
I do your dirty work.

13:04.017 --> 13:06.419
And what's your plan?

13:06.453 --> 13:08.455
[ Imitates Explosion ]

13:08.488 --> 13:10.958
- A bomb?
- No.

13:10.991 --> 13:15.428
I need a garage,
welding supplies,
and a few of your men.

13:15.462 --> 13:18.131
And?

13:18.165 --> 13:21.801
When I'm done, you can
drag the Butcher
through the streets.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.106
Grey's stable,
but he's still
in a lot of pain.

13:26.139 --> 13:29.642
He's landing at 1700.
When can we see him?

13:29.676 --> 13:31.778
- Doc says he'll be out
in a week.
- And Hector?

13:31.811 --> 13:34.882
You all know the drill.
And I thank you all
for your help.

13:38.318 --> 13:42.189
I don't think
I'm the best person.
These are the orders.

13:42.222 --> 13:45.959
- Hector's family?
- I gave his parents
your address.

13:45.993 --> 13:48.828
They're gonna come by
and collect Hector's key.

13:48.862 --> 13:51.131
- I'll tell Annie.
- How close were they?

13:51.164 --> 13:53.200
- He wanted to marry her.
- Did she know
what his work was?

13:53.233 --> 13:55.202
She was ex-army. Two tours.

13:55.235 --> 13:57.670
She didn't hear the words,
but she knew.

14:07.347 --> 14:10.083
Annie, I--

14:13.020 --> 14:14.988
I have news about Hector.

14:15.022 --> 14:17.324
Bad news.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.192
Annie, he's gone.

14:22.029 --> 14:25.832
- Oh, I'm sorry, Tiffy.
- You're sorry?

14:25.865 --> 14:28.068
You knew him for years.
He was just a guy I met.

14:28.101 --> 14:33.006
- He was in love with you.
- Yeah, well, not me.

14:33.040 --> 14:35.508
Never fall in love
with a soldier--

14:35.542 --> 14:38.378
Especially one pretending
to be a logistics clerk.
That was my rule.

14:38.411 --> 14:40.413
That's a good rule.

14:43.416 --> 14:45.718
Um, what happened?

14:45.752 --> 14:49.022
- They'll never tell us.
- And you're okay with that?

14:49.056 --> 14:51.858
- I'm getting used to it.
- Yeah, well, not me.

14:51.891 --> 14:54.294
You know what I liked
about Hector?
That he was--

14:56.729 --> 14:59.099
- That he was
a straight shooter.
- Right from the heart.

14:59.132 --> 15:01.969
You want a tequila shot?
Yeah.

15:06.639 --> 15:08.575
Sorry.

15:12.980 --> 15:16.049
That's water, baby.
That's water. Come on.

15:16.083 --> 15:19.286
Shh. Shh, shh.

15:35.002 --> 15:39.906
Sergeant, I'm the M.E.,
Captain Bowen.

15:39.939 --> 15:42.075
Let's see what we got here.

15:42.109 --> 15:44.444
This is your buddy's
chest cavity.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.747
Got a foreign object
right here.
A bullet.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.749
And you were there
when it was fired?

15:49.782 --> 15:51.985
Yes, sir.

15:52.019 --> 15:54.321
With your permission,
I need to handle the body.

15:57.324 --> 16:01.628
Looks like it came
through the neck here,
snapping the cerebral cortex.

16:01.661 --> 16:04.097
He wouldn't have felt anything.

16:04.131 --> 16:08.801
- Then into the chest cavity,
where it lodged here.
- That's what we figured.

16:08.835 --> 16:11.104
Downward angle through here.

16:11.138 --> 16:13.373
Sniper.

16:15.042 --> 16:18.111
- I'm gonna need the bullet.
- Of course.

16:18.145 --> 16:21.148
- What's the cover story?
- Play 16.

16:21.181 --> 16:25.285
I'll issue the death
certificate, and we'll
prepare the remains for burial.

16:25.318 --> 16:27.287
No traces of Beirut
on the body.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.289
We'll take care of him,
Sergeant,

16:29.322 --> 16:31.191
with respect and reverence.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.395
- I'll stay.
- That's not necessary.

16:36.496 --> 16:38.831
Thank you, sir.
I'll stay.

16:45.338 --> 16:49.142
- That's not the truth.
- What do you want people
to hear? The facts?

16:49.176 --> 16:51.178
- That's right. The facts.
- Okay.

16:51.211 --> 16:54.314
You held a gun
to an American soldier's head.

16:54.347 --> 16:56.349
That's a fact.

16:56.383 --> 16:59.086
You pulled the trigger.
How's that for a creative
headline?

17:03.356 --> 17:06.593
- The gun wasn't loaded.
- You didn't know that.

17:09.262 --> 17:11.931
You have one of our secrets,
and we have one of yours.

17:15.902 --> 17:18.071
You want to trade?

17:19.206 --> 17:22.709
Those are his
personal bodyguards.

17:22.742 --> 17:25.011
That would indicate
that he's in there.

17:25.044 --> 17:28.215
He's inside.
I can get you close to him.

17:29.282 --> 17:32.519
- Slowly.
- Slowly works.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.721
All except the slow part.

17:34.754 --> 17:37.890
There's a lot of men.
There's more inside.

17:37.924 --> 17:40.360
They will die for him.

17:40.393 --> 17:43.363
You turning shy?

17:43.396 --> 17:47.234
Revenge is a dangerous thing,
my friend.

17:47.267 --> 17:50.770
And I will not send my men
to die for another man's anger.

17:50.803 --> 17:54.407
I'll go in first.
You don't like what you see,
turn around and go home.

17:54.441 --> 17:57.277
[ Chuckling ]

17:57.310 --> 17:59.246
You are serious?

18:07.154 --> 18:10.089
[ Men Chattering
In Arabic ]

18:23.303 --> 18:26.639
This mongrel sold you out
to the Butcher.

18:26.673 --> 18:28.608
[ Man Speaks Arabic ]

18:28.641 --> 18:30.310
- [ Groans ]
- [ Laughing ]

18:30.343 --> 18:33.413
- What do you suggest
I do to him?
- He's your problem.

18:33.446 --> 18:36.583
He gave you up.
It's not safe to go.

18:36.616 --> 18:39.452
He'll have more security.

18:39.486 --> 18:43.956
Because of this mongrel,
the Butcher will now
expect you and kill you.

18:43.990 --> 18:46.326
I'm still going.

18:46.359 --> 18:49.596
He's your problem, not mine.
[ Gun Cocks ]

18:49.629 --> 18:53.200
Here's how I solve my problems.

18:54.334 --> 18:56.969
Now he's someone else's problem.

19:14.854 --> 19:17.657
Granger.

19:17.690 --> 19:19.859
Granger, what are you doing?
Give me that.

19:19.892 --> 19:22.329
What is this?

19:24.231 --> 19:28.301
You're a murderer.
You publish these words,
they'd just kill people.

19:28.335 --> 19:30.303
They'd get me killed,
and they'd get you killed.

19:30.337 --> 19:32.472
- You gave me your word.
- I didn't give you anything.

19:32.505 --> 19:35.642
- I don't have anything to give.
- Make sense of this.

19:35.675 --> 19:39.679
There are people ready to
declare you an enemy combatant
right now just to shut you up.

19:39.712 --> 19:42.482
- Do you want to vanish?
- You're threatening me.

19:42.515 --> 19:44.517
No, I'm not threatening you.
I'm your friend.

19:44.551 --> 19:46.886
I'm the only friend you got.
But I'm losing my patience.

19:46.919 --> 19:49.822
Then I want some something.

19:49.856 --> 19:52.692
If I'm gonna chuck
my journalism degree,
I want something.

19:52.725 --> 19:58.064
- What?
- The guy who died--
your friend--

19:58.097 --> 20:00.667
Be very careful.
Who was he?

20:00.700 --> 20:02.702
What was he like?

20:04.737 --> 20:07.340
You don't deserve it.

20:07.374 --> 20:09.342
Something.
You're not worthy
of knowing his name.

20:09.376 --> 20:12.111
Something, please,
to make this real.

20:14.046 --> 20:15.882
Please.

20:18.451 --> 20:20.420
White House?

20:20.453 --> 20:23.890
N.S.C. It was my mission--
The oversight.

20:23.923 --> 20:27.427
So I feel
connected to you...

20:27.460 --> 20:30.062
and your colleague,
Sgt. Williams.

20:30.096 --> 20:33.533
You want water?

20:33.566 --> 20:35.234
Ice cubes?
Anything?

20:37.604 --> 20:40.407
So you caught a bullet, huh?
Yes, sir.

20:42.575 --> 20:47.580
I just wanted
to drop by in person
to offer our thanks.

20:47.614 --> 20:49.582
But I'm not here.

20:49.616 --> 20:51.651
Just as you weren't there.

20:53.486 --> 20:55.755
I need to make sure
we're all on the same page.

20:55.788 --> 20:58.725
What page is that again?

20:58.758 --> 21:02.729
You were there,
and you took the hit.
Your friend took the hit.

21:02.762 --> 21:05.565
We're a team
from the top down.

21:05.598 --> 21:08.601
- I want to make sure
we've got it straight.
- Got it straight?

21:08.635 --> 21:11.103
That none of it occurred.

21:16.676 --> 21:20.647
You mean my friend,
Hector Williams?

21:20.680 --> 21:24.250
Who was a good soldier?
None of that occurred?

21:24.283 --> 21:26.486
Easy enough, right?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.523
[ Glass Shatters ]

21:34.293 --> 21:36.929
I'm looking
for the senior chaplain.

21:36.963 --> 21:38.798
Uh, I'm a chaplain.
Not the senior one.

21:38.831 --> 21:41.300
Will the senior chaplain
be back?

21:41.334 --> 21:43.436
Well, there's a war happening.
That's where he is.

21:43.470 --> 21:45.472
Colonel Ryan's command
issued a request
for the chapel...

21:45.505 --> 21:48.107
for Thursday
at 1200 hours.

21:48.140 --> 21:51.778
Uh, he authorized me
to have the paperwork.

21:51.811 --> 21:53.980
Hmm.

21:54.013 --> 21:55.982
Please.

21:58.851 --> 22:01.954
The deceased was
with the 303rd Logistics.

22:01.988 --> 22:04.123
- Sgt. Hector Williams.
- You're related
to the deceased?

22:04.156 --> 22:07.326
No. He worked with my husband.

22:07.360 --> 22:09.829
The body will be sent
to his hometown.
Yes, sir.

22:09.862 --> 22:12.532
His family elected
to bury him in a family plot.

22:12.565 --> 22:14.634
He could've been buried
at Arlington.
Yes, sir.

22:14.667 --> 22:17.136
And we'd like to do
the memorial service for
the Unit here at the chapel.

22:17.169 --> 22:19.706
Uh, we're doing a group
memorial in two weeks.

22:19.739 --> 22:22.709
I'm sorry.
Did you say group memorial?
It's army policy.

22:22.742 --> 22:24.811
We're short staffed
and this is...

22:24.844 --> 22:26.679
our 63rd memorial service
so far this year.

22:26.713 --> 22:28.815
If you want to look
for a later date,
that's what's available.

22:28.848 --> 22:31.317
No.

22:31.350 --> 22:33.720
We're authorized
for a memorial service.

22:33.753 --> 22:36.823
Colonel Ryan can confirm that.
If you want me to call him--

22:36.856 --> 22:38.991
No, ma'am.

22:39.025 --> 22:41.661
The last thing I need to do
is bother a colonel.

22:41.694 --> 22:44.163
As far as getting
the chapel ready,
I'll do what I can.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.032
But we ran out of candles
two months ago.

22:46.065 --> 22:48.535
I don't even have a budget
for Windex.

22:48.568 --> 22:51.904
I am sorry for your loss,
but my staff is me.

22:53.039 --> 22:55.374
Your staff just doubled.

23:24.771 --> 23:26.906
[ Whirring ]

23:32.645 --> 23:35.615
So--

23:35.648 --> 23:38.985
At this press conference,

23:40.587 --> 23:42.622
what do you want me to say?

23:42.655 --> 23:44.757
What did Jesus say
to the Revlon lady?

23:44.791 --> 23:46.893
"Don't talk to me about nails."

23:46.926 --> 23:50.429
[ Chuckles ]
You're a writer.

23:50.463 --> 23:53.065
Make up a daring escape.
Write your ticket.

23:53.099 --> 23:55.568
You're the hero of the story.
That's what you really wanted,
isn't it?

23:55.602 --> 23:57.136
No.

23:59.939 --> 24:02.108
What I wanted...

24:03.442 --> 24:05.745
was to show the people
the tragedy happening there.

24:05.778 --> 24:09.115
Well, the truth...

24:09.148 --> 24:12.251
is talk shows,
lecture circuits,

24:12.284 --> 24:14.621
a million dollar book deal.

24:14.654 --> 24:17.824
Think about it.
You didn't become a priest.
You became a journalist.

24:17.857 --> 24:22.094
A man escapes from
a half a dozen armed guards.

24:22.128 --> 24:24.096
People want to hear that story.

24:24.130 --> 24:26.165
You tell that story,

24:26.198 --> 24:29.301
and people listen to that man
if he wants to talk
about Lebanon.

24:32.138 --> 24:36.108
I plan to press
disciplinary actions.
And you were up there--

24:36.142 --> 24:38.110
Checking his cover story.
And why?

24:38.144 --> 24:39.946
To make sure--
To make sure that what?
He held his water?

24:39.979 --> 24:41.948
That's right.

24:41.981 --> 24:44.617
What do you got
in your pockets?
Empty them out.

24:44.651 --> 24:47.186
Are you kidding?
No. Empty 'em.

24:50.056 --> 24:52.024
Where's your body bag?

24:52.058 --> 24:53.793
I don't have a body bag.
Exactly.

24:53.826 --> 24:56.128
But each soldier in the Unit
carries their own body bag.

24:56.162 --> 25:00.132
And until you carry one,
you don't deserve to talk
to my men about their code.

25:00.166 --> 25:03.670
They signed on to not exist.
For them, there is no legacy.

25:03.703 --> 25:06.305
These men die for each other.
Not for you or for your boss.

25:06.338 --> 25:09.141
These men are warriors.

25:09.175 --> 25:12.545
You think you need
to remind them
about their codes of silence?

25:12.579 --> 25:15.514
They answer
to a higher code, friend.

25:15.548 --> 25:18.050
Let's keep
this meeting on point.
Your man attacked me.

25:18.084 --> 25:20.486
A seriously wounded man
on his back attacked you?

25:20.519 --> 25:23.189
Yes.

25:23.222 --> 25:25.992
Well, he may have
dinged your ear,
but I'll break your jaw.

25:26.025 --> 25:27.594
Now get the hell off my base.

25:31.898 --> 25:34.100
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

25:58.257 --> 26:00.559
[ Shouting In Arabic ]

26:05.297 --> 26:07.233
[ Groans ]

26:18.477 --> 26:20.613
[ Groans ]

26:27.920 --> 26:29.722
[ Groans ]

26:29.756 --> 26:31.824
Hello, Butcher.
Come on down.

26:42.168 --> 26:44.436
[ Man Shouts In Arabic ]

26:54.681 --> 26:57.984
[ Rebel Leader ]
We'll take the Butcher and you.

27:02.154 --> 27:04.256
We had an understanding.

27:04.290 --> 27:06.659
Things change.
[ Speaking Arabic ]

27:06.693 --> 27:09.128
You owe me for Tripoli.

27:09.161 --> 27:11.931
The Butcher's death
will even the debt.

27:11.964 --> 27:14.667
Your last act on earth...

27:14.701 --> 27:17.103
will be to see your enemy die.

27:17.136 --> 27:19.105
[ Jonas ]
He murdered my friend.

27:19.138 --> 27:21.140
Let me have the honor
of killing him.
[ Groans ]

27:22.842 --> 27:26.278
No, he's right.

27:26.312 --> 27:28.214
One last gift.

27:30.149 --> 27:33.352
Imagine
how this will play...

27:33.385 --> 27:35.154
all over the world.

27:59.879 --> 28:02.181
- [ Groans ]
- [ Gunshots ]

28:08.020 --> 28:10.056
[ Shouting In Arabic ]

28:36.548 --> 28:38.417
[ Beeps ]

28:51.931 --> 28:53.933
We got a boat to catch.

29:10.582 --> 29:12.451
Hey.

29:14.787 --> 29:17.589
Got your message.

29:17.623 --> 29:20.893
I just got all these things
going on in my head.
Me too.

29:20.927 --> 29:23.429
I didn't know where else
to go but here.

29:23.462 --> 29:25.764
You were with him.

29:25.798 --> 29:28.600
He just kept telling me
I'd make it.

29:31.503 --> 29:33.639
And we talked about you.

29:33.672 --> 29:36.442
You know, he was--
He was crazy about you.

29:38.444 --> 29:41.113
Me too, about him.

29:46.618 --> 29:48.620
I just needed to say that
to somebody.

29:48.654 --> 29:50.456
Hey, he knew.

29:54.626 --> 29:57.096
- Look, I need your help.
- Anything.

29:57.129 --> 29:59.131
- Can you help me
get out of here?
- No way, soldier.

29:59.165 --> 30:01.333
You were a medic.
Yeah, and do no harm to others.

30:01.367 --> 30:04.436
- You broke your scapula and
you have internal bleeding.
- Just take these out--

30:04.470 --> 30:06.272
You're gonna need that
for the pain.
Okay, okay.

30:06.305 --> 30:08.107
Hey, hey, hey. Hey.
Hey, look at me.

30:08.140 --> 30:11.477
Where exactly do you think
you're going?

30:11.510 --> 30:14.446
Hector's parents are here,
at the apartment.

30:14.480 --> 30:17.516
For how long?
I don't know. But they're
packing up his things.

30:17.549 --> 30:20.719
I need to see them.
I promised him.

30:53.685 --> 30:55.988
Good morning.

30:56.022 --> 30:59.225
Mrs. Brown. Your service
isn't for two days.

30:59.258 --> 31:02.494
I know.
I bought supplies
for your other services.

31:02.528 --> 31:04.696
Flowers, candles--

31:04.730 --> 31:06.732
Windex.
[ Chuckles ]

31:06.765 --> 31:08.600
You bought those?

31:09.902 --> 31:13.539
Yeah, Mrs. Brown,
I held a sunrise service...

31:13.572 --> 31:15.741
in the woods this morning
for 19 Wiccans.

31:15.774 --> 31:18.044
All army.

31:18.077 --> 31:20.012
Now that's my job.
Serve all faiths.

31:20.046 --> 31:22.248
Why are you doing this?

31:22.281 --> 31:24.750
I want it to be
a good service--

31:24.783 --> 31:26.852
for all of them.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.721
Well, then you're a good woman.
No, I'm not good.

31:37.296 --> 31:41.533
Every time my husband
goes on a mission, I pray.

31:41.567 --> 31:43.435
That's good.
No.

31:45.604 --> 31:48.074
I pray that if
someone has to die,

31:49.241 --> 31:51.143
that it won't be him.

31:52.979 --> 31:55.781
If someone dies,

31:55.814 --> 31:58.050
I feel relieved--

31:58.084 --> 32:01.420
for my baby,
for my family--

32:01.453 --> 32:03.455
that it wasn't him.

32:06.492 --> 32:09.395
This time...

32:09.428 --> 32:12.431
God answered my prayer
with one of my husband's
friends.

32:15.167 --> 32:17.469
God answered my prayer.

32:22.274 --> 32:24.643
[ Rattling ]

32:30.983 --> 32:34.253
Uh, Mr. and Mrs. Williams,
I'm Charles Grey.

32:34.286 --> 32:37.923
- You were Hector's best friend.
- Yes, sir.
And we shared this apartment.

32:37.956 --> 32:40.592
I'm sorry.
We just wanted
to get his things.

32:40.626 --> 32:42.928
No. No, ma'am.
I understand.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.998
[ Mr. Williams ]
Do you want
to sit down, son?

32:46.032 --> 32:49.968
- No, sir. Not quite yet.
- [ Weeping ]

32:50.002 --> 32:53.172
- You were wounded.
- Yes, ma'am.

32:53.205 --> 32:56.942
With my son?
Yes, sir.

32:56.975 --> 32:59.045
- They didn't tell us.
- No, ma'am. They wouldn't.

33:01.813 --> 33:06.018
Look, I wanted
to see you personally.

33:06.052 --> 33:08.654
I promised Hector I would.

33:10.222 --> 33:11.890
I know he'd have done
the same for me.

33:13.825 --> 33:15.494
Thank you.

33:16.895 --> 33:18.830
I made a pot of coffee.

33:18.864 --> 33:20.666
Uh, I'd love that.

33:22.668 --> 33:24.903
You were with Hector
when he died?

33:27.406 --> 33:30.509
Look, I'm not gonna lie to you.

33:32.744 --> 33:35.347
There are things
that I can't tell you.

33:35.381 --> 33:37.649
And I'm not going to lie to you.

33:37.683 --> 33:40.519
I don't need the details.
Just the essence.

33:42.088 --> 33:45.091
The essence, sir, is...

33:46.392 --> 33:48.760
your son saved my life.

33:52.398 --> 33:54.933
We captured the Butcher.

33:57.203 --> 34:01.240
Killed?
Captured.

34:01.273 --> 34:03.609
It was our mission,
just like saving you.

34:07.713 --> 34:09.681
That thing--
that didn't happen.

34:09.715 --> 34:11.550
You remember that?

34:13.585 --> 34:15.554
That's right.

34:19.891 --> 34:22.528
Now as I mentioned before.
We're not privy to that
information.

34:22.561 --> 34:25.197
Sorry.
[ Bob ]
You ready?

34:25.231 --> 34:27.366
The press is just
on the other side.

34:27.399 --> 34:31.069
Yes. He's coming in
in just a moment.
He's in good health.

34:31.103 --> 34:32.904
He liked ice in his beer.

34:34.273 --> 34:37.609
The man who died--
My friend.

34:40.446 --> 34:42.414
He liked ice in his beer.

34:50.956 --> 34:53.892
[ Man ]
Hey, there he is.
[ Man #2 ] Marc Granger.

34:53.925 --> 34:55.727
Mr. Granger.
Mr. Granger, over here.
[ Shouting Questions ]

34:55.761 --> 34:58.797
[ Muffled Chattering ]

34:58.830 --> 35:01.833
Mr. Granger?
[ Indistinct ]

35:04.303 --> 35:07.506
As his commanding officer,
I need you to sign this form
releasing his body.

35:16.615 --> 35:18.517
It's been an honor.

35:26.958 --> 35:28.994
He's awfully pretty.

35:30.862 --> 35:32.831
Always was.

36:00.492 --> 36:03.028
Time to go home, Hector.

36:20.379 --> 36:23.582
Detail, attention.

36:29.421 --> 36:31.357
Present arms.

36:45.937 --> 36:47.873
Quarter arms.

36:59.751 --> 37:01.853
You brought him home.

37:01.887 --> 37:04.055
That's a sacred duty.
Well done.

37:07.626 --> 37:10.629
I knew you'd go back.
You played me.

37:11.797 --> 37:15.401
I know you.
Not going back wasn't an option.

37:17.936 --> 37:19.605
He was like a brother
to me, Colonel.

37:27.145 --> 37:29.381
Thanks for coming.

37:29.415 --> 37:31.817
Makes a lot of stuff
seem unimportant.

38:09.120 --> 38:13.759
Do Unit citations
go flush or above?

38:13.792 --> 38:15.461
Flush with the pocket seam.

38:17.496 --> 38:20.031
And are you gonna put
his regimental insignia
on his uniform?

38:21.132 --> 38:23.134
Yes.

38:24.302 --> 38:26.438
And where's his home regiment?

38:26.472 --> 38:28.374
18th Infantry.

38:32.478 --> 38:35.013
"In omnia paratus."

38:37.983 --> 38:39.651
"In all things prepared."

38:42.988 --> 38:45.023
No medals, right?

38:45.056 --> 38:48.527
Ribbons, yes. Medal, no.

38:51.697 --> 38:54.332
He has a silver and bronze star.

38:54.366 --> 38:58.470
- Mm-hmm.
- And a purple heart.

38:58.504 --> 39:00.839
And he'll be getting
another purple heart?

39:08.013 --> 39:10.181
His parents will.

39:51.122 --> 39:53.224
[ Woman On TV,
Indistinct ]

40:05.904 --> 40:08.239
What are you doing?

40:09.240 --> 40:11.577
I'm spit-shining jump boots.

40:11.610 --> 40:15.046
- You shouldn't spit.
- I need to see myself in them.

40:15.080 --> 40:17.315
[ TV Continues ]

40:20.486 --> 40:22.888
When are we going to tell her?

40:22.921 --> 40:27.125
Marc Granger was a hostage
for months in war torn Lebanon.

40:27.158 --> 40:30.061
Marc, you escaped
single-handedly.

40:30.095 --> 40:32.798
You got yourself out of Beirut.

40:32.831 --> 40:35.467
- How does it feel to be
an instant hero?
- I'm not.

40:35.501 --> 40:38.069
There's talk of a book.
Maybe even a movie deal.

40:38.103 --> 40:40.071
How does it all make you feel?
Lucky.

40:40.105 --> 40:42.307
Very lucky.

40:42.340 --> 40:46.311
But being a prisoner
for so long gave me
a lot of time to think...

40:46.344 --> 40:48.446
about the political
situation in Lebanon.
That's good enough.

40:48.480 --> 40:50.181
And I would like--
Not yet, it's not.

41:02.127 --> 41:04.462
Hey.

41:04.496 --> 41:07.132
Came to get my, uh,
dress uniform.

41:07.165 --> 41:09.134
Uh--

41:10.468 --> 41:13.104
I moved it.

41:13.138 --> 41:16.174
You being here without an M.P.
could get you fired.

41:16.207 --> 41:18.844
I guess I'm counting on you
not to turn me in.

41:23.314 --> 41:25.350
Mmm.

41:27.318 --> 41:29.287
Tiffy--

41:29.320 --> 41:31.322
Shh.

41:32.558 --> 41:34.225
[ Whispering ]
Quiet.

41:49.741 --> 41:52.043
[ Sobs ]

41:55.681 --> 41:58.383
I need you to get this
in Hector Williams's
hometown newspaper.

41:59.851 --> 42:02.220
"First Class Sergeant
Hector Williams...

42:02.253 --> 42:06.491
"was transporting documents
across an airfield
in Turkey...

42:06.524 --> 42:10.195
"when an unexploded
ordnance blew up,
rolling his jeep.

42:10.228 --> 42:12.330
"He died instantly.

42:12.363 --> 42:16.668
"303rd Logistics Unit,
Fort Griffith Command,

42:16.702 --> 42:19.370
expresses their condolences."

42:19.404 --> 42:21.372
His whole life he's been
defending his country,

42:21.406 --> 42:23.241
and at the end,
that's what he's gonna get?

42:23.274 --> 42:26.244
That's Play 16.
Run it.

43:00.411 --> 43:04.049
[ Chaplain ]
"And what greater love
hath any man...

43:04.082 --> 43:07.552
but to give his life
for his brothers?"

43:07.585 --> 43:09.454
Amen.

43:23.101 --> 43:26.437
- Blane.
- Here, sir.

43:28.940 --> 43:31.977
- Gerhardt.
- Here, sir.

43:32.010 --> 43:35.580
- Grey.
- Here, sir.

43:35.613 --> 43:39.484
- Brown.
- Here, sir.

43:41.452 --> 43:43.955
Williams.

43:55.300 --> 43:58.369
Sergeant Williams.

44:04.710 --> 44:08.346
"Sergeant First Class
Hector Williams.

44:08.379 --> 44:12.818
"Born November 16, 1976.

44:14.185 --> 44:17.555
"Oldest son of
George and Carol Williams.

44:18.990 --> 44:22.393
Killed in action."
